FBIS4-8853 "dreeu075_i_94013" FBIS-EEU-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues Casualty Figures Reported LD1804191894 Lisbon RTP Internacional Television in Portuguese 1800 GMT 18 Apr 94 LD1804191894 Lisbon RTP Internacional Television Portuguese BFN [Excerpts] The city of Gorazde fell to the Serbs this afternoon. [passage omitted] The UNHCR has its hands tied, it can do nothing to protect the 60,000 Muslims of Gorazde. [UNHCR spokesman Manuel Almeida on the telephone, identified by caption] Up until last night the number of casualties was 302 dead and 1,075 injured. Yesterday alone, 37 people died and 73 were injured. [passage omitted]
